Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm wedges (no need to peel).

Pop them onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%mins}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

== Mushroom Sauce ==

Peel and grate the @garlic{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @mushrooms{125%grams}.

Place a #pot{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. When hot, fry the mushrooms until softened, ~{4-5%mins}.

Add the @creme fraiche{65%grams}, garlic, @Worcester sauce{1%sachet} and @water{25%ml} (double for 4p). Bring to the boil.

Simmer until the mushrooms are softened and the sauce has thickened, ~{6-8%mins}. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Set aside and cover to keep warm.

== Burgers ==

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, combine the @breadcrumbs{1%pack}, 2 tsp @water{2%tsp} and ¼ tsp @salt{1/4%tsp} (double both for 4p).

Add the @Irish Beef Mince{250%grams}, season with @pepper{to taste} and mix everything together with your hands. Roll into evenly-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Once hot, fry the burgers until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{10-12%mins}. Turn every 2-3 mins, lowering the heat if needed.

> IMPORTANT: Burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat. Place some @Grated Italian Style Hard Cheese{25%grams} on top of each burger then cover the pan and set aside (off the heat) until the cheese melts, ~{3-4%mins}.

== Assembly ==

When everything is almost ready, pop the @Brioche Buns{2} into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%mins}. Thinly slice the @tomato{1}.

> TIP: Keep an eye on the buns so they don't burn!

To assemble the burgers, spread a spoonful of mushroom sauce over each base bun. Top with the beef burger, remaining mushroom sauce and sliced tomato. Close with the top bun.

Serve with the chunky potato wedges alongside.